  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study to evaluate whether (1) targeted smoke alarm education, (2) general
      fire safety education with a smoke alarm component, (3) basic fire safety education, or (4)
      an unrelated intervention is most effective way to improve smoke alarm maintenance and
      function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
